	(107,1,'2012-02-07 20:20:41','2012-02-07 20:20:41','When I was three-months-old, my mom took me to the doctor for what she thought was a cold; however, she learned that I had a condition called cardiomyopathy, a deadly heart disease that could only be remedied by a heart transplant. I spent nine weeks on the waiting list and received a transplant on Mother\'s Day in 1992. Ten years passed and my body started to reject the heart. I was placed back on the waiting list and more than a year later, I received my second heart transplant on July 18, 2005. I want to thank Donor Alliance for all their work in improving the number of organ donors. If it weren\'t for Donor Alliance\'s essential understanding of the public brought forth through awareness, I and many other recipients I know might not be alive.','Conner','','publish','closed','closed','','conne','','','2012-02-13 21:26:34','2012-02-13 21:26:34','',0,'http://donor.stage.lrxd.com/?post_type=recipient&#038;p=107',7,'recipient','',0),
