	(179,1,'2012-02-13 18:50:29','2012-02-13 18:50:29','<em>Aftercare for Donor Families:</em>\r\n\r\nAftercare services provided for donor family members are a vital part of Donor Alliance’s mission. Emily Herbst, our Aftercare Coordinator, works closely with donor families to provide initial bereavement materials and referrals to support groups.\r\n\r\nEmily is available for donor families to help answer questions that may arise after the donation including: updated information about the recipients of their loved ones’ organ donation, assistance with correspondence between donor families and recipients and updates on tissue placement.\r\n\r\nResources for Donor Families:\r\n<a title=\"Local Grief Support\" href=\"http://donor.stage.lrxd.com/?page_id=85\">• Local grief support\r\n</a>• <a href=\"http://www.donoralliance.org/online_resources\">Web sites offering grief support resources for donor families\r\n</a>• <a href=\"http://www.donoralliance.org/online_griefwords_library\">Online Griefwords Library by Dr. Alan Wolfelt, Ph.D.\r\n</a>• <a href=\"http://www.donoralliance.org/donor_family_quilt_project\">Donor Family Quilt Project</a>\r\n• <a href=\"http://www.donoralliance.org/corresponding_with_organ_recipients\">Corresponding with organ recipients\r\n</a>\r\nEmily Herbst can be reached at:\r\nDirect: 303-370-2737\r\nToll free: 888-868-4747','Donor Family Resources','','publish','open','open','','donor-family-resources','','','2012-02-16 21:55:42','2012-02-16 21:55:42','',173,'http://donor.stage.lrxd.com/?page_id=179',3,'page','',0),
